Welcome to my GitHub project website.

My name is Diana Hackenburg and I am a PhD student in the Rubenstein School at the University of Vermont. I study the connections between human well-being and nature, as well as communication, education and community action related to the environment, specifically algal blooms. Before coming to Vermont, I worked as a science writer/editor with North Carolina Sea Grant, as well as with Triangle Land Conservancy, Virginia Department of Environmental Quality, and the Blue Ridge Land Conservancy. Check out my other website or email me.
